{"questionId":"13977409","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>.&nbsp;Justify your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>for the scales to balance, the odd ball must be in the six balls not chosen&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>for the scales to balance, all the balls chosen must be of equal weight and hence</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13977409","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2ei","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of x. Justify your answer.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}